abstract = {There are regional imbalances in the construction of sustainable development in China, and a framework needs to be proposed to measure it. In this study, a similarity measurement framework based on granular computing is prosed to measure the imbalances of China's provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities) oriented to goals 1, 3, 8, 10, and 15 of the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs). The framework takes each county as the calculation sample and uses atomic formulas to granulate information for each index of the index system, and the similarity problem among different provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities) is evaluated from the bottom to the top through scale transformation. The framework is a new paradigm for analysing social system research problems from a part to the whole and from the details to the abstract. Based on similarity measurement calculations, most of China's provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities) have little similarity in sustainable development, China's sustainable development exhibits regional imbalance.}
